entries.arrival_phase_1: pcontrast3 Beissa: < pcontrast1 Stand by, they will be in any moment.  pcontrast3 >
entries.arrival_phase_2: pcontrast3 Beissa: < pcontrast1 Something odd... their hyperspace signature is only a 97% match.  Barely outside the margin for error, but we don't get old by being careless.  Watch your back. pcontrast3 >
entries.assassinate_success: pcontrast3 Beissa: < pcontrast1 I don't like it. That was too easy. pcontrast3 >
entries.destroy_escort: Leave no one left alive, pilot! Destroy the target's escort, now.
entries.escort_remaining: pcontrast3 Tactical Computer: < pcontrast1 An escorting craft has been destroyed, %DI remain. pcontrast3 >
entries.escort_wiped_out: pcontrast3 Tactical Computer: < pcontrast1 All escorting craft have been destroyed. pcontrast3 >
entries.failed_escape: One of Valarian's new hired killers managed to elude capture. Mission failed!
entries.quest_escort_d: The escort is unimportant to your mission for this target, ignore them.
entries.quest_location_d: Deep space near the gas giant Yavin
entries.quest_target_d: A Rodian fighter pilot, works cheap because he loves his job
entries.split_quest_alert: pcontrast3 Beissa: < pcontrast1 Just as I suspected, that was a decoy.  Here comes the real Valarian Replacement. pcontrast3 >
entries.title: Yavin System: Hunt down Valarian replacements
entries.title_d: Destroy the Valarian pilots hired to replace you, part 3 of 3
